    {
      "court_date": "2010-04-05 9:00 AM",
      "matters": "ACCOUNTING PETITION RE: ACCOUNTING #1, REPORT, FEES<br>Off Calendar Apr-05-2010 Granted Per Written Order<br>MINI MINUTES: Appearances: George Sullivan in Propria Persona.<br><br>The Court stated that there was no objection, that there was an order approving $5,000.00 for litigation fees to Michael Bassi, and that any further payment of fees to Mr. Bassi needed to have prior Court approval and needed to be justified. In addition, the Court stated that it did not receive a declaration from Mr. Bassi, that it had time sheets but that they were not very helpful, and asked what services were performed by Mr. Bassi and what benefit was provided to the Estate. Mr. Sullivan stated that he felt it was prudent to hire litigation Counsel with regard to the will contest, that Mr. Bassi reviewed six or seven other wills of the Decedent that were close to the same as the one that was submitted for probate, that he corresponded with Counsel Nelson which went on for about 90 days, and that he prevented litigation from going forward. In addition, he stated that Mr. Bassi was able to settle the will contest, that he prepared a number of letters, made a number of phone calls and did research. The matter was taken under submission. <br><br>Judge Pro Temp: Sue M. Kaplan. Reporter: Diana Chen, CSR#11312. Clerk: Rosie Noguera. Bailiff: Deputy F. Smith.<br>",
      "location": "CIVIC CENTER COURTHOUSE ROOM 204",
      "judge": "SUE M. KAPLAN"
    },
